We recommended that Management: 

1. Immediately contact the concerned NGOs to submit liquidation of the active receivables and if the fund remained unutilized, demand its full refund to the LGU; 

2.  File its request for write-off for the dormant accounts as provided in COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016. These accounts also warrant the provision for impairment losses considering the indications that these receivables may no longer be collected by the LGU.

We recommended that Management: 

1. Create the Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory of all PPEs of the Municipality, whether acquired through purchase or donation, including those constructed by administration and found at station; 

2. Thru the Inventory Committee created, update the property records based on the results of physical inventory, and reconcile with accounting records; 

3. Undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular No. 
2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with the reconciled and correct balances of PPE accounts in the financial statements; and 

4. After the inventory taking, direct the Municipal Accountant to update the ledger cards for each item of the PPE pursuant to Section 269 of the GAM for LGUs.

We recommended that Management: 

1. Submit the liquidation documents of the above transactions which includes official receipts or sales/charge invoices; 
2. Stop the payment of financial assistance to the COP of the PNP stationed in the Municipality and all requests should be purchased by the Municipality in accordance with Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations of the Republic Act No. 9184; 

3. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to record the purchase of supplies and equipment as asset of the LGU for proper accounting and establishment of accountability over the items purchased and issued to the PNP personnel assigned to the Municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a. Municipal Accountant to reconcile accounting records of the road network with the complete Local Road Inventory Report containing complete description and cost segregation of the road components and provide proper disclosure of the road networks in the Notes to Financial Statements; 
b. General Service Officer (GSO) to maintain an updated Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card of all roads within its area of jurisdiction;
c. Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of the components of all roads within its area of jurisdiction; and
d. Inventory Committee to conduct inventory of local roads, highways and bridges within its area of jurisdiction which were acquired thru purchase or construction, donations or transfers without cost.

